data.text:
Fifth Avenue, NY, USA

Latitude and longitude coordinates are: 40.773998, -73.966003.

Fifth Avenue is a famous street situated in the very center of New York City, NY, the eastern US. Known as one of the most beautiful and luxury streets of the city, Fifth Avenue begins in Greenwich Village south of Central Park and runs to Harlem. The street is about 6.2 miles long. It is an old street established over 150 years ago and developing as one of the central streets of New York City. A part of Fifth Avenue is known as "Museum Mile" and there is a large number of museums there like the Metropolita Museum of Art, Museum of NYC, the Jewish Museum, Museum of African Art, Neue Gallery of New York City, and so on. There are also plenty of hotels, shops, financial and business centers, famous skyscrapers like the Empire State Building, Rockefeller Center, NY Public Library, Flatrion Building, and others located there.
